WHY AGPL AND NOT MIT:
The AGPLv3 was chosen deliberately. Unlike MIT, AGPLv3 requires that
anyone who runs a modified version of this software as a network
service must also release their modifications as open source under
the same license. This ensures that improvements to the World Contrast
infrastructure remain public and auditable — permanently.

TRADEMARK RESTRICTION (applies regardless of license):
The AGPLv3 grant does NOT include permission to use the name
"World Contrast", "WorldContrast", the logo, or the domain
worldcontrast.org in any fork, derivative work, or competing service.
Forks must clearly identify themselves as independent projects and
may not imply affiliation with, endorsement by, or origin from
the World Contrast Organization.

=======================================================================
PART 2: HISTORICAL DATA AND PUBLIC LEDGER — CC BY 4.0
=======================================================================

The verified political promises, cryptographic hashes, provenance
metadata, source URLs, archive links, and rejection logs (collectively,
the "Historical Data") extracted and validated by the World Contrast
infrastructure are licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0
International License.

Full license text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

You are free to:
  — Share: copy and redistribute the Historical Data in any medium
  — Adapt: remix, transform, and build upon the data
  — Use commercially: including for journalism, research, and analysis

Under the following conditions:
  — Attribution: you must credit "World Contrast Organization" as the
    definitive authenticated source, with a link to worldcontrast.org
  — Hash Integrity: any redistribution of the data must preserve the
    original SHA-256 content hashes. Any alteration that invalidates
    a cryptographic hash nullifies the World Contrast authentication
    and must not be attributed to this organization.
  — No Misrepresentation: you may not present altered, filtered, or
    selectively curated subsets of the data as the "complete"
    World Contrast record.

The CC BY 4.0 license applies to static database dumps, public API
responses, and data rendered on the public frontend. It does NOT
apply to real-time API streams, webhooks, or live infrastructure
access (see Part 3).

=======================================================================
PART 3: LIVE API AND INFRASTRUCTURE — PROPRIETARY
=======================================================================

The licenses granted in Parts 1 and 2 DO NOT extend to:

  — The live Enterprise API and real-time data pipelines
  — Webhooks and low-latency streaming endpoints
  — The POCVA-01 extraction engine running in production
    (the protocol specification is open; the production instance
    is not)
  — The Supabase production database and its direct access
  — Any authentication tokens, API keys, or service credentials

Access to the live infrastructure is strictly governed by commercial
agreements and the API Terms of Use at:
https://worldcontrast.org/terms

PROHIBITION ON IMPERSONATION:
No entity — individual, organization, or automated system — may:
  — Replicate or mirror the live data stream and present it as an
    official or real-time World Contrast node
  — Claim to be an authorized World Contrast data provider without
    explicit written authorization from the World Contrast Organization
  — Use the World Contrast authentication seal, hash verification
    interface, or POCVA-01 branding in any unauthorized system

Violations of this section may constitute trademark infringement,
unfair competition, and misrepresentation under applicable law.

=======================================================================
PART 4: DATA PROTECTION AND JURISDICTION
=======================================================================

All data collected and processed by World Contrast relates exclusively
to public figures acting in their public capacity as political
candidates. Collection is performed under:

  — GDPR Article 85, Recital 153 (public interest / journalism)
  — GDPR Article 9(2)(e) (data manifestly made public by the subject)
  — LGPD Brazil Art. 7º, IX (legitimate interest, electoral transparency)

World Contrast operates as a non-profit independent initiative.
It accepts no advertising, no political funding, and no compensation
from any candidate, party, or government entity.

Jurisdiction for disputes: Brazil (LGPD) and, where applicable,
the European Union (GDPR).

